reviews.review_text: - Spectacular moments, and many of them, but in a string of spectacular shows this one stands out as not-as-good. Some heavy clunking during Scarlet Fire, and the post-UJB "space" (really a Garcia solo that seems rather aimless) feels more anticlimactic than anything else.

Agreed Only in the context of the previous and following weeks can this show be seen in a negative light :)  A low point for the dead in May 77 is still a remarkable performance.  There can only be so many great shows in a row...nice work Charlie and definitely worth a listen as there are some great moments here.
